%% Idiomatic Rust Builder — consuming self, fluent, validated at build()
classDiagram
    class HttpClient {
        +endpoint: String
        +timeout: Duration
        +retries: u8
        +builder() HttpClientBuilder
    }
    class HttpClientBuilder {
        -endpoint: Option~String~
        -timeout: Option~Duration~
        -retries: Option~u8~
        +endpoint(String) Self
        +timeout(Duration) Self
        +retries(u8) Self
        +build() Result~HttpClient, BuildError~
    }
    class BuildError {
        <<enum>>
        MissingEndpoint
        RetriesTooHigh(u8)
    }

    HttpClient ..> HttpClientBuilder : factory method
    HttpClientBuilder ..> HttpClient : constructs
    HttpClientBuilder ..> BuildError : returns on failure

    note for HttpClientBuilder "Every setter takes self by value and\nreturns Self. The builder is #[must_use]\nso ignoring the chain is a warning.\nbuild() validates required fields and\nreturns Result — never Option, never unwrap."
